# üõ†Ô∏è Installation Guide ‚Äî Membit Context Agent (V61)

This guide explains how to install and run the Membit Context Agent locally.
Works on Linux, macOS, Windows (WSL), and mobile (Termux / Replit).

---

## ‚úÖ 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/alarsabandy7-lab/Membit-Cluster-Agent
cd Membit-Cluster-Agent
```

## ‚úÖ 2. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate        # Linux / macOS

# Windows (PowerShell)
# .venv\Scripts\activate
```

## ‚úÖ 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -U discord.py aiohttp python-dotenv google-generativeai
```

## ‚úÖ 4. Create & Configure .env
Create File:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Then edit:

```bash
DISCORD_TOKEN=your_discord_token
MEMBIT_API_KEY=your_membit_key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key   # optional
COOLDOWN_SECONDS=12
```

##‚úÖ 5 . Run

```bash
python main.py
```

